  "text": "Models of texture segregation have concentrated on identifying the basic mechanisms that must underlie this ability [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Graham et al., 1992; [CITATION_4] . The present study seeks to compliment these analyses by introducing both isotrigon textures and formal statistical discriminant models. Part of the concept behind the discriminant models is to compare quadratic and linear models given a fairly limited number of samples, as the human subjects had in our tests. A secondary objective was to see if either type of discriminant model would show behaviour that was anything like that of human subjects.",
